gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Raptors 111, Wizards 107
gameRecap.excerpt: The Raptors overcame a 23-point deficit from early in the 3rd quarter and ended the game on a 21-1 run to defeat the Wizards, 111-107. Pascal Siakam totaled a season-high 39 points to go along with 11 rebounds and seven assists as Scottie Barnes added 19 points, nine rebounds, five steals, and four assists for the Raptors. Kyle Kuzma scored a season-high 34 points while Daniel Gafford added 14 points and nine rebounds for the Wizards. The Raptors improve to 5-5 while the Wizards move to 2-8 on the year.
